name: Keep Left Promotional Poster
description: These are the original promotion posters for my 1993 book launch of "Keep Left." Yes, I used to spell my name that way to attract attention and it worked. The problem was that the staff that made these posters on an offset press thought that I meant to put "Take It Or Leave It." Consequently I had to black out the "It" on several hundreds of these with a Sharpie. These will come signed to whomever and saying whatever you want. They will be shipped flat in heavy cardboard to protect them better and save you and I money on shipping costs.

name: "Four Short Films by Corey Hamilton" - DVD
description: This DVD is of four films that Hamilton made in the 90s. Equal parts heavy handed, absurd and informative but all Corey Hamilton. WARNING: THIS DVD HAS GRAPHIC IMAGERY WHICH MAY TO BE SUITABLE FOR ALL VIEWERS! Note: This DVD is compatible with NTSC players.

name: "A Collection of Video Poems by Corey Hamilton" - DVD
description: Just what the title says and it has 120 poems on it read in a variety of locations around Edmonton. The inside booklet has a short write up about C.W.Hamilton by Michael Gravel. Note: This DVD is compatible with NTSC players. COMING SOON!

name: "Sniper" - CD
description: This CD is a re-issue of a bunch of recordings that myself and few friends did. The recordings come from 1991, 1998 & 2002. Spoken word with music. COMING SOON!

name: "For Windows" - CD
description: This CD is a re-issue of some recordings from 2003 that I did with a few friends. It is a spoken word piece taken from an e-book called "No One Shall Be Spared." It is a very harsh look at my time working in a dead end retail job and of the customers who make those sorts of jobs harder than they should be. COMING SOON!

name: Do Not Ever Have Any Good Ideas
description:
"Hamilton’s “Do Not Ever Have Any Good Ideas” reads as if it was written in 6 weeks but it was actually written in only 4."

“….Ideas” has stream of consciousness prose, poetry and even an essay! Either tell Hamilton to knock it off with this constant barrage of words or I will go after him with a pickaxe and do some damage on that guy. Thank you for your cooperation."

Name & address withheld by request.

name: Cease & Desist
description: A journal about the trials and tribulations of doing freelance work for people who sometimes pay and sometimes don't pay.

name: Sensible Shoes
description: This small book was written by Corey Hamilton. It has NO profane words in it and it is very silly, but true. Written in a diary form, it has true stories taken from Hamilton’s embarrassing past, with a hopeful outlook and NO profane language. Part gonzo, part philosophy, it is very absurd and has NO profane words. Fun for the whole family but recommended for ages 11 3/4 up. Did we mention already that it has NO profane words in it?

name: How I Remember It
description: This is a book of stream of consciousness writing. Part philosophy, part Gonzo but all Corey W. Hamilton. 41 pages.

name: Magic Bus
description: This is a stream of consciousness book that was written while riding buses and waiting for buses. Written June through September 2012 & published March 2013. 52 pages.

name: What If?
description: “What If?” is a short and (for the most part) hopeful look at the lives of 6 dead rock stars and asks what if their lives had turned out differently. Written in May 2012 & published July 2012. 24 pages.

name: VI
description: A collection of Corey’s six short stories that were originally published in his paperbacks and e-books. Compiled December 2011 & published April 2012. 70 pages.

name: Thirty Three
description: Thirty poems from Corey’s four paperbacks and six e-books as well as three new poems. Compiled in November 2011 and published in December 2011. 74 pages.

name: Time Marches On
description: Stream of consciousness prose/poetry. An artistic journal written by an artist in love with another artist. Written September 2010 through March 2011 & published August 2011. 46 pages.

name: 2 Days
description: Poetry taken from 1990 to 2010 with illustrations from Corey’s 1980’s era notebooks. Compiled July 2010  & published February 2011. 163 pages. Free shipping on this book on all Canadian orders!

name: Unhyped
description:
Completed May 2010
Published September 2010
Written Piece #1777
16 page, 8.5 × 11 chapbook
Text with full colour pictures.

"Autobiography"
C.W.Hamilton Interviewed by Hunter S. Thompson.

name: Exit Is A Safe Place
description: A collection of poetry & prose taken from 1986-1993 with an essay written sometime in the late 90's. The stream of consciousness piece with the same title as the book itself, is based on Corey’s grief of losing his Grandfather Hamilton. Compiled April 1993  & published October 2005. 144 pages.

name: Society's Grip
description: A collection of poetry & prose form 1986 to 1993. The stream of consciousness piece, “SARAH” is based on Corey’s successful attempt to quit drugs and alcohol. Compiled April 1993  & published May 1999. 163 pages.

name: Keep Left
description: A collection of poetry & prose from 1986 to 1993 including a play called “Scene From The Other Side.” Compiled April 1993  & published in May 1993 with a second printing in May 1999. 88 pages. Illustrations by Andrea Baeza.

name: Dramatic Situations 20th Anniversary Shirt
description:
Use the code "SHIRTSALE5" & get $5 off this puppy! While supplies last of course.
Only 20 shirts were made. 

All shirts were tested on animals. They didn't fit.

name: "Here's Lookin' At You" - 7" Blue Vinyl EP
description:
Limited Edition Blue 7" Vinyl
Released in September of 2005.

Words, voice - Corey Hamilton / Music, trickery - Randall Edwards.

Comes with a free download of both songs.

name: Hollyhocks Painting
description: This is a painting of Hollyhocks on an 8” x 10” stretched canvas. Some of you may know that I really enjoy painting flowers and because this is a small piece I will place it here for sale. It is shipped in a heavy box with packing as well as some free goodies. Shipping prices are extremely expensive so they do come with insurance. Thanks for your interest!

name: Clowning Around #111
description: This piece is an original piece of art made with acrylics & paper. It is painted on 10” x 10” stretched canvas and it is part of the “Clowning Around Series.” I took old photographs of myself, printed them on paper and attached to the canvas using medium and paint. Originally there were 10 of them but some of them have sold. I placed a word on each canvas with a corresponding number with the though in mind that some people misuse or use ideas against other people. By using an image of myself with clown paint I was trying to say that it could be anyone doing this and that they are a clown for those thoughts & actions. These are shipped in a heavy box with packing as well as some free goodies. Shipping prices are extremely expensive so they do come with insurance. Thanks for your interest!
